  "text": "Bisulfite genomic sequencing. Bisulfite genomic sequencing was carried out on genomic DNA samples that were bisulfite converted using the EZ DNA methylation kit (Zymo Research) as previously described [CITATION_1] . Primers and annealing temperatures used to amplify bisulfite converted genomic DNA are listed in Supplementary Table S3. COMPARE methylation assay. A variation of the previously described COMPARE-MS assay [CITATION_2] , termed the COMPARE (combination of methylated DNA precipitation and restriction enzyme digestion) assay, was used to determine the degree of CpG island methylation at candidate hypomethylated genes and at LINE1 consensus promoter sequences in the prostate cell line and tissue samples. The COMPARE assay is identical to the COMPARE-MS assay except that the methylation-sensitive restriction enzyme was omitted [CITATION_3] . A detailed description of the COMPARE assay can be found in supplementary materials, with PCR primers listed in Supplementary Table S4 .",
